<p>GDP growth: 2.8% GDP: $1,396bn (PPP: $963bn) Inflation: 2.8% Population: 22.9m GDP per head: $61,040 (PPP: $42,130)</p>

<p>The second-term Labor government's fragile majority may not survive the year, and early elections are on the cards. The government's vulnerability is reflected in the divisive proposal for a carbon tax, promised in return for the vote of parliament's only Green member, but contravening a pre-election pledge by the prime minister, Julia Gillard. The government's economic programme was eroded by the flooding of 2010 and 2011; resources will be diverted to recovery work, but strong commodities earnings will help growth.</p>

